        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1535228892" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12535943025759442965">This was exactly what I needed. A fun, easy read with a good story. It&apos;s really for middle-grade kids but middle-grade...middle-age...close enough right? <br/><br/>Poor Jax has just lost his father making him an orphan. He&apos;s been sent to live with Riley, who&apos;s barely old enough to take care of himself. He soon learns there is an extra day between Wednesday and Thursday. It was created by a magic spell long ago and <a class='jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction'>(view spoiler)</a><span class='spoilerContainer' style='display: none'>[ only descendants of the original Round-Table Knights are able to live throug</span></span>
  <span id="freeText12535943025759442965" style="display:none">This was exactly what I needed. A fun, easy read with a good story. It's really for middle-grade kids but middle-grade...middle-age...close enough right? <br /><br />Poor Jax has just lost his father making him an orphan. He's been sent to live with Riley, who's barely old enough to take care of himself. He soon learns there is an extra day between Wednesday and Thursday. It was created by a magic spell long ago and <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[ only descendants of the original Round-Table Knights are able to live through our regular week plus the extra day. The extra day is used to trap people. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span> Some want to get rid of the extra day, others want to eliminate normal time. Who wins? <br /><br />This is book one in a trilogy. It was quite enjoyable to read so I can't wait to get the next one. Recommended for....well, everyone. <br /><br /> </span>
